President Biden and Prime Minister Modi of India will hold a virtual meeting to strengthen ties between the two countries. They will discuss cooperation on various issues, including ending the COVID-19 pandemic, addressing the climate crisis, boosting the global economy, and promoting a free and open international order. The leaders will also talk about the Indo-Pacific Economic Framework and infrastructure development. President Biden will seek India's input on the ongoing conflict between Russia and Ukraine and its impact on global food supply and commodity markets. This meeting will precede the U.S.-India 2+2 Ministerial involving top officials from both countries.